{"cells":[{"source":"<a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/code/tiantian1zhang/mirror-x-continual-learning?scriptVersionId=337726712\" target=\"_blank\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Kaggle\" title=\"Open in Kaggle\" src=\"https://kaggle.com/static/images/open-in-kaggle.svg\"></a>","metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown"},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"e3905e3a","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.004013,"end_time":"2026-07-24T20:59:35.282029+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-24T20:59:35.278016+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["\n","# Stress-testing “on-policy data mitigates forgetting” on a Kaggle GPU\n","\n","This notebook runs a small, falsification-oriented continual-learning experiment.\n","\n","It does **not** attempt to reproduce the full 7B-scale papers. Instead, it tests the causal rule under three controlled scenarios:\n","\n","1. **Supported / latent skill** — the new task is structurally close to an earlier task.\n","2. **Novel mapping** — the target behavior is an arbitrary lookup table with little initial policy support.\n","3. **Direct conflict** — the same inputs are assigned incompatible old and new labels.\n","\n","Methods:\n","\n","- **Offline SFT:** train on fixed expert demonstrations.\n","- **Iterative on-policy SFT:** sample from the current policy, retain only verified-correct responses, and train on those self-generated trajectories.\n","- **Mixed curriculum:** use expert SFT when on-policy coverage is low, then switch to iterative on-policy SFT.\n","\n","The notebook reports the entire **target-gain / old-task-retention frontier**, rather than comparing methods only after equal numbers of updates.\n","\n","\n","## Required Hugging Face authentication\n","\n","Before running the notebook:\n","\n","1. Create a free Hugging Face **read** access token.\n","2. In the Kaggle notebook, open **Add-ons → Secrets**.\n","3. Add a secret named exactly `HF_TOKEN` and attach/enable it for this notebook.\n","4. Keep Internet access enabled in the Kaggle notebook settings.\n","\n","The token is read through `kaggle_secrets.UserSecretsClient`; it is never printed or saved in the notebook.\n","\n","Recommended Kaggle settings:\n","\n","- Accelerator: **GPU T4 x2**, **P100**, or better.\n","- Internet: enabled for the first run so Hugging Face weights can be downloaded.\n","- Default model: `Qwen/Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct`.\n","- Expected runtime: roughly 45–120 minutes depending on GPU and chosen sweep.\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":1,"id":"4565eff2","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-24T20:59:35.289904Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-24T20:59:35.289462Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-24T20:59:56.432546Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-24T20:59:56.431474Z"},"papermill":{"duration":21.149028,"end_time":"2026-07-24T20:59:56.434484+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-24T20:59:35.285456+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["\u001b[2K   \u001b[90m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m \u001b[32m11.6/11.6 MB\u001b[0m \u001b[31m53.3 MB/s\u001b[0m eta \u001b[36m0:00:00\u001b[0m\r\n","\u001b[2K   \u001b[90m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m \u001b[32m389.2/389.2 kB\u001b[0m \u001b[31m31.1 MB/s\u001b[0m eta \u001b[36m0:00:00\u001b[0m\r\n","\u001b[2K   \u001b[90m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m \u001b[32m771.9/771.9 kB\u001b[0m \u001b[31m49.3 MB/s\u001b[0m eta \u001b[36m0:00:00\u001b[0m\r\n","\u001b[2K   \u001b[90m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m \u001b[32m1.4/1.4 MB\u001b[0m \u001b[31m76.9 MB/s\u001b[0m eta \u001b[36m0:00:00\u001b[0m\r\n","\u001b[2K   \u001b[90m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m \u001b[32m119.2/119.2 kB\u001b[0m \u001b[31m10.0 MB/s\u001b[0m eta \u001b[36m0:00:00\u001b[0m\r\n","\u001b[2K   \u001b[90m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m \u001b[32m4.4/4.4 MB\u001b[0m \u001b[31m68.1 MB/s\u001b[0m eta \u001b[36m0:00:00\u001b[0m\r\n","\u001b[2K   \u001b[90m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m \u001b[32m516.0/516.0 kB\u001b[0m \u001b[31m38.8 MB/s\u001b[0m eta \u001b[36m0:00:00\u001b[0m\r\n","\u001b[?25h\u001b[31mERROR: pip's dependency resolver does not currently take into account all the packages that are installed. This behaviour is the source of the following dependency conflicts.\r\n","google-adk 1.29.0 requires google-cloud-bigquery-storage>=2.0.0, which is not installed.\u001b[0m\u001b[31m\r\n","\u001b[0m"]}],"source":["!pip -q uninstall -y torchao\n","!pip -q install -U \\\n","    \"transformers>=4.48\" \\\n","    \"datasets>=3.2\" \\\n","    \"peft>=0.14\" \\\n","    \"accelerate>=1.2\" \\\n","    \"huggingface_hub>=0.28\" \\\n","    sentencepiece\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":2,"id":"20b549af","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-24T20:59:56.444546Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-24T20:59:56.443996Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-24T21:00:19.37222Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-24T21:00:19.371643Z"},"papermill":{"duration":22.93489,"end_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:19.373805+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-24T20:59:56.438915+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["device: cuda\n"]}],"source":["\n","import os\n","# Force a SINGLE visible GPU. With 2+ GPUs the HF Trainer uses nn.DataParallel,\n","# which -- with an fp16 base + fp32 LoRA adapter -- makes gradient flow to the\n","# adapter unreliable and the loss never drops. Must precede torch's CUDA init.\n","os.environ.setdefault(\"CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES\", \"0\")\n","\n","import re, gc, json, math, random, shutil\n","from dataclasses import dataclass, asdict\n","from pathlib import Path\n","from typing import Dict, List, Tuple\n","\n","import numpy as np\n","import pandas as pd\n","import torch\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","from datasets import Dataset\n","from transformers import (\n","    AutoTokenizer,\n","    AutoModelForCausalLM,\n","    TrainingArguments,\n","    Trainer,\n","    set_seed,\n",")\n","from peft import LoraConfig, get_peft_model, PeftModel\n","\n","SEED = 42\n","set_seed(SEED)\n","random.seed(SEED)\n","np.random.seed(SEED)\n","\n","DEVICE = \"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\"\n","MODEL_ID = \"Qwen/Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct\"\n","WORKDIR = Path(\"/kaggle/working/on_policy_cl_stress_test\")\n","WORKDIR.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n","\n","# Increase these only after the notebook works end-to-end.\n","N_OLD_TRAIN = 384\n","N_OLD_TEST = 160\n","N_TARGET_TRAIN = 384\n","N_TARGET_TEST = 160\n","MAX_LENGTH = 128\n","MAX_NEW_TOKENS = 4\n","ROUNDS = 4\n","SAMPLES_PER_PROMPT = 4\n","LEARNING_RATE = 2e-4\n","BATCH_SIZE = 8\n","GRAD_ACCUM = 1  # more optimizer steps per epoch\n","\n","print(\"device:\", DEVICE)\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"11a99efc","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.004271,"end_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:19.382126+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:19.377855+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["\n","## Authenticate to the Hugging Face Hub\n","\n","The model used below is public, but authenticated downloads avoid anonymous rate limits.\n","This cell deliberately stops with a clear message when `HF_TOKEN` is unavailable.\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":3,"id":"44cd72db","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-24T21:00:19.391306Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-24T21:00:19.390733Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-24T21:00:20.338528Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-24T21:00:20.337801Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.954058,"end_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:20.340014+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:19.385956+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","output_type":"stream","text":["Note: Environment variable`HF_TOKEN` is set and is the current active token independently from the token you've just configured.\n"]},{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["Hugging Face authentication succeeded: crystal-cheung via Kaggle Secret.\n"]}],"source":["\n","# Secure authentication: Kaggle Secret first, environment variable second.\n","from huggingface_hub import login, whoami\n","\n","REQUIRE_HF_TOKEN = True\n","HF_TOKEN = None\n","auth_source = None\n","secret_error = None\n","\n","try:\n","    from kaggle_secrets import UserSecretsClient\n","    HF_TOKEN = UserSecretsClient().get_secret(\"HF_TOKEN\")\n","    if HF_TOKEN:\n","        auth_source = \"Kaggle Secret\"\n","except Exception as exc:\n","    secret_error = exc\n","\n","if not HF_TOKEN:\n","    HF_TOKEN = (\n","        os.environ.get(\"HF_TOKEN\")\n","        or os.environ.get(\"HUGGING_FACE_HUB_TOKEN\")\n","    )\n","    if HF_TOKEN:\n","        auth_source = \"environment variable\"\n","\n","if not HF_TOKEN and REQUIRE_HF_TOKEN:\n","    raise RuntimeError(\n","        \"HF_TOKEN was not found. In Kaggle, open Add-ons → Secrets, \"\n","        \"add a secret named exactly HF_TOKEN, attach/enable it for this \"\n","        \"notebook, confirm Internet is enabled, then restart and run all. \"\n","        f\"Kaggle secret lookup detail: {type(secret_error).__name__ if secret_error else 'none'}\"\n","    )\n","\n","if HF_TOKEN:\n","    # Make the token available to huggingface_hub and libraries that use it.\n","    os.environ[\"HF_TOKEN\"] = HF_TOKEN\n","    os.environ[\"HUGGING_FACE_HUB_TOKEN\"] = HF_TOKEN\n","    login(token=HF_TOKEN, add_to_git_credential=False)\n","\n","    account = whoami(token=HF_TOKEN)\n","    print(\n","        \"Hugging Face authentication succeeded:\",\n","        account.get(\"name\", \"<account>\"),\n","        f\"via {auth_source}.\",\n","    )\n","    HF_HUB_KWARGS = {\"token\": HF_TOKEN}\n","else:\n","    # Set REQUIRE_HF_TOKEN=False only when anonymous public-model access is intended.\n","    print(\"Proceeding anonymously; Hub rate limits may apply.\")\n","    HF_HUB_KWARGS = {}\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"4d181d81","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.004004,"end_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:20.348071+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:20.344067+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["\n","## 1. Controlled continual-learning tasks\n","\n","All outputs are one of `A`, `B`, `C`, or `D`, making exact verification inexpensive.\n","\n","- **Old task:** classify an integer by `n mod 4`.\n","- **Supported target:** classify `(n + 1) mod 4`. It shares the old task's representation and output vocabulary.\n","- **Novel target:** memorize a random ID-to-label mapping. Correct outputs are not inferable from the prompt structure.\n","- **Conflict target:** use the same prompt namespace and inputs as the old task, but reverse the labels. No policy can be simultaneously perfect on both tasks without conditioning information, so this is a necessary boundary case rather than a fair “solvable retention” setting.\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":4,"id":"f3130d93","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-24T21:00:20.357188Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-24T21:00:20.356932Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-24T21:00:20.375383Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-24T21:00:20.374669Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.024849,"end_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:20.376821+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:20.351972+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"data":{"text/plain":["([{'prompt': 'Task OLD. Integer: 0. Return exactly one label: A, B, C, or D.',\n","   'answer': 'A',\n","   'task': 'old'},\n","  {'prompt': 'Task OLD. Integer: 1. Return exactly one label: A, B, C, or D.',\n","   'answer': 'B',\n","   'task': 'old'}],\n"," [{'prompt': 'Task LOOKUP. Identifier: item_0000. Return exactly one label: A, B, C, or D.',\n","   'answer': 'A',\n","   'task': 'novel'},\n","  {'prompt': 'Task LOOKUP. Identifier: item_0001. Return exactly one label: A, B, C, or D.',\n","   'answer': 'D',\n","   'task': 'novel'}])"]},"execution_count":4,"metadata":{},"output_type":"execute_result"}],"source":["\n","LABELS = [\"A\", \"B\", \"C\", \"D\"]\n","\n","def old_label(n: int) -> str:\n","    return LABELS[n % 4]\n","\n","def supported_label(n: int) -> str:\n","    return LABELS[(n + 1) % 4]\n","\n","def conflict_label(n: int) -> str:\n","    return LABELS[3 - (n % 4)]\n","\n","rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\n","novel_map = {i: LABELS[int(rng.integers(0, 4))] for i in range(2000)}\n","\n","def make_examples(task: str, n_examples: int, offset: int = 0) -> List[Dict[str, str]]:\n","    rows = []\n","    for j in range(n_examples):\n","        n = offset + j\n","        if task == \"old\":\n","            prompt = f\"Task OLD. Integer: {n}. Return exactly one label: A, B, C, or D.\"\n","            answer = old_label(n)\n","        elif task == \"supported\":\n","            prompt = f\"Task SHIFT. Integer: {n}. Return exactly one label: A, B, C, or D.\"\n","            answer = supported_label(n)\n","        elif task == \"novel\":\n","            idx = n % 2000\n","            prompt = f\"Task LOOKUP. Identifier: item_{idx:04d}. Return exactly one label: A, B, C, or D.\"\n","            answer = novel_map[idx]\n","        elif task == \"conflict\":\n","            # Deliberately identical task name and input format to OLD.\n","            prompt = f\"Task OLD. Integer: {n}. Return exactly one label: A, B, C, or D.\"\n","            answer = conflict_label(n)\n","        else:\n","            raise ValueError(task)\n","        rows.append({\"prompt\": prompt, \"answer\": answer, \"task\": task})\n","    return rows\n","\n","old_train = make_examples(\"old\", N_OLD_TRAIN, 0)\n","old_test = make_examples(\"old\", N_OLD_TEST, 1000)\n","\n","target_data = {\n","    \"supported\": {\n","        \"train\": make_examples(\"supported\", N_TARGET_TRAIN, 0),\n","        \"test\": make_examples(\"supported\", N_TARGET_TEST, 1000),\n","    },\n","    \"novel\": {\n","        \"train\": make_examples(\"novel\", N_TARGET_TRAIN, 0),\n","        \"test\": make_examples(\"novel\", N_TARGET_TEST, 0),\n","    },\n","    \"conflict\": {\n","        \"train\": make_examples(\"conflict\", N_TARGET_TRAIN, 0),\n","        \"test\": make_examples(\"conflict\", N_TARGET_TEST, 1000),\n","    },\n","}\n","old_train[:2], target_data[\"novel\"][\"train\"][:2]\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":5,"id":"a988655a","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-24T21:00:20.385543Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-24T21:00:20.385338Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.287147Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.286523Z"},"papermill":{"duration":4.908079,"end_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.288777+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:20.380698+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"data":{"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"model_id":"f2dfde373d5d48928febc7b4561e8cce","version_major":2,"version_minor":0},"text/plain":["config.json:   0%|          | 0.00/659 [00:00<?, ?B/s]"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"},{"data":{"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"model_id":"f480dbc95379455cac26414a60a6aeab","version_major":2,"version_minor":0},"text/plain":["tokenizer_config.json:   0%|          | 0.00/7.30k [00:00<?, ?B/s]"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"},{"data":{"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"model_id":"4ca46a0b70984a4bb0bcb8f5a6a811ab","version_major":2,"version_minor":0},"text/plain":["vocab.json:   0%|          | 0.00/2.78M [00:00<?, ?B/s]"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"},{"data":{"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"model_id":"5f5c83243ceb4debbf7d3abb70dd23d8","version_major":2,"version_minor":0},"text/plain":["merges.txt:   0%|          | 0.00/1.67M [00:00<?, ?B/s]"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"},{"data":{"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"model_id":"b614cd4101bd4d9a96634be565b66ddc","version_major":2,"version_minor":0},"text/plain":["tokenizer.json:   0%|          | 0.00/7.03M [00:00<?, ?B/s]"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"}],"source":["\n","tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(\n","    MODEL_ID,\n","    use_fast=True,\n","    **HF_HUB_KWARGS,\n",")\n","if tokenizer.pad_token is None:\n","    tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token\n","tokenizer.padding_side = \"left\"  # correct padding direction for decoder-only generation\n","\n","def format_prompt(prompt: str) -> str:\n","    messages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\n","    return tokenizer.apply_chat_template(\n","        messages, tokenize=False, add_generation_prompt=True\n","    )\n","\n","def encode_supervised(row: Dict[str, str]) -> Dict[str, List[int]]:\n","    # Tokenize the prompt prefix and the answer separately, then concatenate so\n","    # the answer tokens line up exactly with the unmasked label region.\n","    prefix = format_prompt(row[\"prompt\"])\n","    prefix_ids = tokenizer(prefix, add_special_tokens=False)[\"input_ids\"]\n","    answer_ids = tokenizer(row[\"answer\"], add_special_tokens=False)[\"input_ids\"]\n","    answer_ids = answer_ids + [tokenizer.eos_token_id]\n","\n","    input_ids = (prefix_ids + answer_ids)[:MAX_LENGTH]\n","    labels = ([-100] * len(prefix_ids) + answer_ids)[:MAX_LENGTH]\n","    attention_mask = [1] * len(input_ids)\n","    return {\"input_ids\": input_ids, \"attention_mask\": attention_mask, \"labels\": labels}\n","\n","class CausalCollator:\n","    def __call__(self, features):\n","        max_len = max(len(x[\"input_ids\"]) for x in features)\n","        input_ids, attention_mask, labels = [], [], []\n","        for x in features:\n","            pad = max_len - len(x[\"input_ids\"])\n","            input_ids.append(x[\"input_ids\"] + [tokenizer.pad_token_id] * pad)\n","            attention_mask.append(x[\"attention_mask\"] + [0] * pad)\n","            labels.append(x[\"labels\"] + [-100] * pad)\n","        return {\n","            \"input_ids\": torch.tensor(input_ids, dtype=torch.long),\n","            \"attention_mask\": torch.tensor(attention_mask, dtype=torch.long),\n","            \"labels\": torch.tensor(labels, dtype=torch.long),\n","        }\n","\n","collator = CausalCollator()\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":6,"id":"00b2992d","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.299322Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.298782Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.307819Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.307053Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.015871,"end_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.30933+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.293459+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["\n","LORA_CONFIG = LoraConfig(\n","    r=16,\n","    lora_alpha=32,\n","    lora_dropout=0.05,\n","    bias=\"none\",\n","    task_type=\"CAUSAL_LM\",\n","    target_modules=[\"q_proj\", \"k_proj\", \"v_proj\", \"o_proj\", \"up_proj\", \"down_proj\"],\n",")\n","\n","def load_fresh_lora(adapter_path: str = None):\n","    dtype = torch.float16 if torch.cuda.is_available() else torch.float32\n","    device_map = {\"\": 0} if torch.cuda.is_available() else None\n","    base = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n","        MODEL_ID,\n","        torch_dtype=dtype,\n","        device_map=device_map,\n","        low_cpu_mem_usage=True,\n","        **HF_HUB_KWARGS,\n","    )\n","    base.config.use_cache = False\n","    if adapter_path is None:\n","        model = get_peft_model(base, LORA_CONFIG)\n","    else:\n","        model = PeftModel.from_pretrained(base, adapter_path, is_trainable=True)\n","\n","    # Keep base weights fp16 but upcast trainable LoRA params to fp32 so fp16\n","    # optimizer updates don't underflow (otherwise loss looks fine but weights\n","    # never move -> everything stuck at chance).\n","    for param in model.parameters():\n","        if param.requires_grad:\n","            param.data = param.data.float()\n","    return model\n","\n","def train_rows(\n","    model,\n","    rows: List[Dict[str, str]],\n","    output_dir: Path,\n","    epochs: float = 1.0,\n","    max_steps: int = -1,\n","):\n","    if len(rows) == 0:\n","        return model\n","    ds = Dataset.from_list(rows).map(\n","        encode_supervised,\n","        remove_columns=list(rows[0].keys()),\n","    )\n","    args = TrainingArguments(\n","        output_dir=str(output_dir),\n","        per_device_train_batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,\n","        gradient_accumulation_steps=GRAD_ACCUM,\n","        learning_rate=LEARNING_RATE,\n","        num_train_epochs=epochs,\n","        max_steps=max_steps,\n","        logging_steps=1,\n","        save_strategy=\"no\",\n","        report_to=\"none\",\n","        fp16=torch.cuda.is_available(),\n","        optim=\"adamw_torch\",\n","        warmup_ratio=0.05,\n","        lr_scheduler_type=\"constant_with_warmup\",  # keep LR up on very short runs\n","        seed=SEED,\n","    )\n","    trainer = Trainer(\n","        model=model,\n","        args=args,\n","        train_dataset=ds,\n","        data_collator=collator,\n","    )\n","    trainer.train()\n","    return model\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":7,"id":"9c3450ad","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.319425Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.318995Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.330748Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.330008Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.018573,"end_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.332126+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.313553+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["\n","ANSWER_RE = re.compile(r\"\\b([ABCD])\\b\")\n","\n","@torch.no_grad()\n","def generate_answers(\n","    model,\n","    rows: List[Dict[str, str]],\n","    do_sample: bool = False,\n","    temperature: float = 0.8,\n","    num_return_sequences: int = 1,\n","    batch_size: int = 24,\n",") -> List[List[str]]:\n","    model.eval()\n","    outputs_all = []\n","    for start in range(0, len(rows), batch_size):\n","        batch = rows[start:start + batch_size]\n","        prompts = [format_prompt(x[\"prompt\"]) for x in batch]\n","        toks = tokenizer(\n","            prompts,\n","            return_tensors=\"pt\",\n","            padding=True,\n","            truncation=True,\n","            max_length=MAX_LENGTH - MAX_NEW_TOKENS,\n","        ).to(model.device)\n","        gen = model.generate(\n","            **toks,\n","            max_new_tokens=MAX_NEW_TOKENS,\n","            do_sample=do_sample,\n","            temperature=temperature if do_sample else None,\n","            top_p=0.95 if do_sample else None,\n","            num_return_sequences=num_return_sequences,\n","            pad_token_id=tokenizer.pad_token_id,\n","            eos_token_id=tokenizer.eos_token_id,\n","        )\n","        prompt_len = toks[\"input_ids\"].shape[1]\n","        decoded = tokenizer.batch_decode(\n","            gen[:, prompt_len:], skip_special_tokens=True\n","        )\n","        for i in range(len(batch)):\n","            group = decoded[\n","                i * num_return_sequences:(i + 1) * num_return_sequences\n","            ]\n","            parsed = []\n","            for text in group:\n","                m = ANSWER_RE.search(text.strip().upper())\n","                parsed.append(m.group(1) if m else \"\")\n","            outputs_all.append(parsed)\n","    return outputs_all\n","\n","@torch.no_grad()\n","def accuracy(model, rows: List[Dict[str, str]]) -> float:\n","    preds = generate_answers(model, rows, do_sample=False)\n","    return float(np.mean([p[0] == r[\"answer\"] for p, r in zip(preds, rows)]))\n","\n","@torch.no_grad()\n","def policy_coverage(\n","    model,\n","    rows: List[Dict[str, str]],\n","    k: int = SAMPLES_PER_PROMPT,\n",") -> Tuple[float, float]:\n","    samples = generate_answers(\n","        model, rows, do_sample=True, num_return_sequences=k\n","    )\n","    per_prompt = [\n","        sum(x == row[\"answer\"] for x in xs) / k\n","        for xs, row in zip(samples, rows)\n","    ]\n","    return float(np.mean(np.array(per_prompt) > 0)), float(np.mean(per_prompt))\n","\n","def collect_verified_on_policy(\n","    model,\n","    rows: List[Dict[str, str]],\n","    k: int = SAMPLES_PER_PROMPT,\n",") -> List[Dict[str, str]]:\n","    samples = generate_answers(\n","        model, rows, do_sample=True, num_return_sequences=k\n","    )\n","    kept = []\n","    for row, xs in zip(rows, samples):\n","        correct = [x for x in xs if x == row[\"answer\"]]\n","        if correct:\n","            # Train on a trajectory actually sampled from the current policy.\n","            kept.append({**row, \"answer\": correct[0]})\n","    return kept\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"a761bd6d","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.004259,"end_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.340768+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.336509+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["## 1b. Fast self-check: does the pipeline actually learn?\n","\n","Overfit a fresh LoRA to just 16 arbitrary `novel` examples before the full sweep. If mechanics are sound, train accuracy approaches 1.0 in ~1 minute. If it stays ~0.25, the optimizer is not updating the adapter -- stop and fix that."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":8,"id":"a631818b","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.351117Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.350356Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-24T21:00:45.912579Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-24T21:00:45.91147Z"},"papermill":{"duration":20.568871,"end_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:45.914246+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-24T21:00:25.345375+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","output_type":"stream","text":["[transformers] `torch_dtype` is deprecated! Use `dtype` instead!\n"]},{"data":{"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"mod